  "texts": [
    "There are two primary forms of collaborative filtering: user-based and item-based.",
    "User-based collaborative filtering entails identifying users with akin preferences and suggesting items that these users have favored.",
    "When User A and User B possess similar purchase histories, items that User A has purchased and liked will be recommended to User B.",
    "In contrast, item-based collaborative filtering identifies resemblances between items and recommends items that are akin to those appreciated by a user.",
    "For example, if a customer enjoys a particular book, the system will propose other books that share similar content or genres."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}